@startuml
title Viaverse Analytics / Observability / Product Intelligence — Use Case Diagram
left to right direction

actor "Client Apps" as Client
actor "Backend Services" as Services
actor "Product / Engineering" as Team
actor OpenTelemetry as Otel
actor "Prometheus / Perses" as Metrics
actor "OpenSearch / Jaeger" as Logs

rectangle "Analytics / Observability Boundary" {
  usecase "Track product event" as Track
  usecase "Apply consent/privacy\nPII minimization" as Consent
  usecase "Create anonymous/session ID" as Session
  usecase "Ingest analytics event" as Ingest
  usecase "Collect distributed trace" as Trace
  usecase "Collect metrics\nRED/USE/SLO" as Metric
  usecase "Collect structured logs" as Log
  usecase "Correlate trace/log/event\ncorrelationId" as Correlate
  usecase "View dashboards" as Dashboard
  usecase "Alert on SLO/error/anomaly" as Alert
  usecase "Analyze funnel\nactivation/conversion" as Funnel
  usecase "Analyze experiment impact" as Experiment
  usecase "Monitor data quality" as Quality
  usecase "Apply retention / deletion" as Retention
  usecase "Emit analytics events\nDataQualityFailed / AlertRaised" as Events
}

Client --> Track
Track --> Consent
Consent --> Session
Session --> Ingest
Services --> Trace
Services --> Metric
Services --> Log
Trace --> Correlate
Metric --> Correlate
Log --> Correlate
Team --> Dashboard
Team --> Alert
Team --> Funnel
Funnel --> Experiment
Ingest --> Quality
Quality --> Retention
Retention --> Events
Otel --> Trace
Metrics --> Metric
Logs --> Log

note bottom
Product analytics must be privacy-safe.
Observability data must be correlated with traceId/correlationId
but must not leak secrets or raw personal data.
end note
@enduml
